# swim-coach PWA (web/) -- build-time environment configuration.
#
# Copy to `.env` in this directory for local dev with `npm run dev` / `npm
# run build` -- Vite auto-loads it. Never commit `.env` -- it's gitignored.
# In CI/deploy (.github/workflows/deploy.yml), this is set as the
# `VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` repository *variable* (not secret -- see below),
# not from a file.

# Google OAuth Client ID for Sign-In (see src/identity.js). This is public,
# not a secret -- Google Identity Services client IDs are meant to be
# embedded in front-end code -- so it's safe as a plain build-time env var
# (Vite only exposes `VITE_`-prefixed vars to client code; this one is
# intentionally client-visible). Register one at
# https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials (OAuth 2.0 Client ID,
# type "Web application"; add both the GitHub Pages origin and
# http://localhost:5173 as authorized JavaScript origins).
#
# Left unset, identity.js falls back to a clearly-labeled placeholder so
# `npm run build` still succeeds -- Google Sign-In just won't work until
# this is set to a real Client ID.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
